Positions Available
Compliance Officer – Dallas
The Compliance Officer will assist the Chief Compliance Officer with managing the firm’s compliance program including, drafting, implementing, monitoring and testing compliance policies and procedures; reviewing and editing communications materials; monitoring vendor due diligence; prepare internal and external compliance certifications; serve as back-up for monitoring and testing trade compliance for client accounts and employee Code of Ethics compliance.
Product Manager – Dallas
The Product Manager is responsible for planning, developing and executing the firm’s “Go-2-Market” strategy ensuring a consistent client experience both visually and operationally to drive sales growth.
Administrative Assistant – Houston
The Administrative Assistant is responsible for assisting Trust officers, Investments and Operations in administering clients trusts and investments. The incumbent will have direct contact via telephone and e-mail with clients, attorneys and CPAs.
 
