2016-10-18T22:10:17+00:00


Parker Young
Mr. Young joined Westwood in 2013 and currently serves as Vice President, Fixed Income Trader.  Mr. Young began his investment career in 2005 with Deutsche Bank Securities Inc. in New York working as an Analyst on the High Yield and Distressed Debt Institutional Sales Desk.  While at Deutsche Bank, Mr. Young worked on a team developing traditional fixed income, credit derivative, and structured product solutions for Institutional Investment Managers.  Prior to joining Westwood, he worked in Institutional Sales at Tejas Securities Group, LLC and GMP Securities, LLC in Dallas, Texas.  Mr. Young earned his BA in Economics, Political Science and Public Policy from Southern Methodist University in Dallas, Texas.
